<subSubSection pageId="97" pageNumber="98" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="97.[151,1437,1061,1267]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1061,1087]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Streets" authorityYear="1872" box="[324,552,1061,1087]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jugosus">
<emphasis box="[324,552,1061,1087]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Petrolisthes jugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small bulky species, characterised by the P1 carpus bearing longitudinal crests on the dorsal surface and four large serrated teeth along the mesial margin (distal-most tooth smallest). It is also the only western Atlantic species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[596,729,1133,1159]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[596,729,1133,1159]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Petrolisthes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a five-plated telson. In life, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Streets" authorityYear="1872" box="[1090,1202,1133,1158]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jugosus">
<emphasis box="[1090,1202,1133,1158]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">P. jugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognised by the carmine-red colouration of the carapace, with two white dots lateral to the cardiac area; the similarly carmin-red P1, with darker fingers and white fingertips; and brown-mottled P2–4 (
<figureCitation box="[951,1035,1204,1231]" captionStart="FIGURE 59" captionStartId="97.[151,250,954,978]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,930]" captionTargetId="figure-20@97.[151,1435,181,930]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURE 59. Petrolisthes jugosus Streets, 1872: male (cl 3.5 mm, cw 3.3 mm) from Isla Grande, Panama (MZUSP 40067), dorsal view [photograph by AA]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532355" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532355/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
; see also 
<figureCitation box="[1143,1243,1205,1231]" captionStart="FIGURE 90" captionStartId="140.[151,250,1624,1648]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,181,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-19@140.[164,1424,181,1601]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 90. Some western Atlantic Porcellanidae (all species reported from Panama or Golfo de Urabá at the Panamanian- Colombian border) photographed in situ: A, Neopisosoma angustifrons (Benedict, 1901), Golfo de Urabá, Colombia; B, Neopisosoma neglectum Werding, 1986, Golfo de Urabá, Colombia; C, Pachycheles tuerkayi Werding &amp; Hiller, 2017, Santa Marta, Colombia; D, Petrolisthes jugosus Streets, 1872, Tayrona, Colombia; E, Petrolisthes tonsorius Haig, 1960, blue colour morph, Bonaire; F, Petrolisthes quadratus Benedict, 1901, Bonaire [photographs courtesy of Juan-Felipe Lazarus-Agudelo (A–D) and Marco Faasse (E, F)]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532436" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532436/files/figure.png" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">Fig. 90D</figureCitation>
and photographs in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rodriguez, I. T. &amp; Hernandez, G. &amp; Felder, D. L." box="[180,426,1240,1267]" pageId="97" pageNumber="98" pagination="544 - 582" refId="ref76152" refString="Rodriguez, I. T., Hernandez, G. &amp; Felder, D. L. (2005) Review of the western Atlantic Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura) with new records, systematic observations, and comments on biogeography. Caribbean Journal of Science, 41 (3), 544 - 582." type="journal article" year="2005">
Rodríguez 
<emphasis box="[304,360,1241,1267]" italics="true" pageId="97" pageNumber="98">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
; 
